message.content:
I need to identify the line item that represents tax accrued but not yet paid in the balance sheet.

Looking at the balance sheet, I notice the line item "Taxes Payable" which represents taxes that have been accrued but not yet paid to the relevant tax authorities.

For this line item:
- Initial amount (as of 2023-12-31): 0.00
- End amount (as of 2024-02-05): 727140.68

This means that at the start of the period, there were no taxes payable, but by the end of the period, the company had accrued $727,140.68 in tax liabilities that had not yet been paid.

```json
{"solution": {'initial value': '0.00', 'end value': '727140.68'}}
```
